<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01 Transitional//EN">
<html>
<head>
<title>Help: Grouping items in the catalog</title>
<meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=iso-8859-1">
<link href="../style.css" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css">
</head>

<body>
<p class="titlebold">Grouping items in the catalog</p>
<p class="text">To edit the groups (each group is displayed under a different
  tab in the catalog) that items are displayed in, open the order site in the
  manager, select Items, and click on &quot;Edit item groups...&quot; in the submenu. </p>
<p class="text">Groups may be added, deleted &#8212; down to one group, 
  and hidden so that they don't appear in the catalog on the order site. </p>
<p class="text">To change which group an item is displayed in, change the &quot;Group
  with...&quot; setting in the Item Properties to the group you want to include it
  with.</p>
</body>
</html>
